# Environment Variables for City Crawler
# This template shows all required environment variables for different build environments

# =============================================================================
# CLIENT-SIDE VARIABLES (accessible in app code)
# These use EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix and are bundled with the app
# =============================================================================

# Clerk Authentication
# Get your publishable key from https://clerk.com
# Go to your Clerk dashboard > API Keys > Publishable Key
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_clerk_publishable_key_here

# Supabase Database
# Get your credentials from https://supabase.com
# Go to your Supabase project > Settings > API
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Google Maps API
# Get your API key from https://console.cloud.google.com/
# Enable Geocoding API and Maps SDK for Android/iOS
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# SERVER-SIDE VARIABLES (for build scripts, migrations, etc.)
# These are NOT bundled with the app and are more secure
# =============================================================================

# Supabase Service Role Key (for server-side operations only)
# NEVER expose this in client-side code
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key_here

# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT-SPECIFIC SETUP
# =============================================================================

# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to .env
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. The app will automatically use these values in development

# ANDROID BUILD (Google Play Console):
# 1. Set environment variables in your CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions, etc.)
# 2. Or use EAS Build with environment variables:
#    eas build --platform android --profile production --non-interactive
# 3. Environment variables are automatically included in the build

# IOS BUILD (App Store):
# 1. Set environment variables in your CI/CD pipeline
# 2. Or use EAS Build with environment variables:
#    eas build --platform ios --profile production --non-interactive
# 3. Environment variables are automatically included in the build

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - Never commit the .env file to version control
# - Use different API keys for development, staging, and production
# - The EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefixed variables are bundled with the app
# - For highly sensitive operations, use server-side API routes
# - Consider using Firebase Functions or AWS Lambda for sensitive keys 